00:00:55.767 --> 00:00:57.532
It is so delicious.

00:00:57.532 --> 00:01:00.016
Now, if you're not familiar
with the acai berry,

00:01:00.016 --> 00:01:03.545
it is a berry that is grown
in the Amazon rainforest,

00:01:03.545 --> 00:01:05.983
and it's also known to be a superfood.

00:01:05.983 --> 00:01:10.302
It's full of antioxidants,
vitamin A, B, C,

00:01:10.302 --> 00:01:13.093
magnesium, calcium,
and all that good stuff

00:01:13.093 --> 00:01:16.641
to keep you looking radiant and beautiful.

00:01:16.641 --> 00:01:19.102
This also makes a great
energizing breakfast,

00:01:19.102 --> 00:01:22.283
and also a nice, cold, and
refreshing healthy snack

00:01:22.283 --> 00:01:24.419
for during the daytime.

00:01:24.419 --> 00:01:26.307
So, to make this, you're
going to need a packet

00:01:26.307 --> 00:01:27.879
of frozen acai berry.

00:01:27.879 --> 00:01:29.574
I found this from my local Sprouts.

00:01:29.574 --> 00:01:32.080
You can also find this
at health food stores,

00:01:32.080 --> 00:01:34.496
or also your local supermarket.

00:01:34.496 --> 00:01:37.236
Granola, I am using organic hemp granola

00:01:37.236 --> 00:01:40.535
that I found from Sprouts,
my local supermarket.

00:01:40.535 --> 00:01:44.202
Milk, you can use dairy, soy, coconut.

00:01:44.202 --> 00:01:48.474
I like to use almond milk. It's
delicious, and it's healthy.

00:01:48.474 --> 00:01:52.793
Fresh and frozen fruits,
I love to have a selection

00:01:52.793 --> 00:01:56.020
of bananas, blueberries, strawberries.

00:01:56.020 --> 00:01:58.667
You can pretty much use anything.

00:01:58.667 --> 00:02:01.477
OK, so we're going to make
enough for two servings,

00:02:01.477 --> 00:02:03.984
and I'm going to start with two packets

00:02:03.984 --> 00:02:06.817
of these frozen acai berries.

00:02:06.817 --> 00:02:09.255
Now I'm going to put some
frozen bananas in here.

00:02:09.255 --> 00:02:11.432
And this is where you can customize this

00:02:11.432 --> 00:02:15.710
and put any other frozen
fruits, or whatever you like.

00:02:15.710 --> 00:02:18.311
Now I'm going to add in just
a little bit almond milk,

00:02:18.311 --> 00:02:22.863
like about 1/3 of a cup
to loosen up the mixture.

00:02:22.863 --> 00:02:25.462
Once you have everything
in, go ahead and blend this.

00:02:25.462 --> 00:02:27.389
It might be a little bit
difficult for you to blend,

00:02:27.389 --> 00:02:30.013
because this is going
to be a thick mixture,

00:02:30.013 --> 00:02:31.522
and it should be thick.

00:02:31.522 --> 00:02:33.776
So, every now and then, just
take a spoon or something

00:02:33.776 --> 00:02:35.121
to loosen up the mixture,

00:02:35.121 --> 00:02:38.117
and then go ahead and
turn on the blender again.

00:02:38.117 --> 00:02:39.417
Once you are done blending,

00:02:39.417 --> 00:02:44.349
go ahead and pour that
deliciousness mixture into a bowl.

00:02:44.349 --> 00:02:46.506
All you have to do now is top this off

00:02:46.506 --> 00:02:48.087
with any toppings of your choice.

00:02:48.087 --> 00:02:52.291
I like granola, bananas,
strawberries, blueberries.

00:02:52.291 --> 00:02:54.055
It's so, so delicious.

00:02:54.055 --> 00:02:56.771
I actually took a break
from editing this video

00:02:56.771 --> 00:03:00.302
and made myself another
bowl of the acai berry bowl.

00:03:00.302 --> 00:03:02.460
So good!

00:03:02.460 --> 00:03:04.968
Alrighty, guys, so are you
