00:03:19.118 --> 00:03:21.696
To make this, you will
need some peanut butter,

00:03:21.696 --> 00:03:25.550
granola, some banana, or an apple.

00:03:25.550 --> 00:03:27.085
To start, peel your banana,

00:03:27.085 --> 00:03:29.056
and then cut it into half like so.

00:03:29.056 --> 00:03:32.516
Next, with the apple, cut
the bottom and the top off,

00:03:32.516 --> 00:03:34.931
then I'm going to cut this into fourths.

00:03:34.931 --> 00:03:37.894
As you can see, I made
this into circular shapes.

00:03:37.894 --> 00:03:41.432
And then I just cut out the
core, so that way, you know,

00:03:41.432 --> 00:03:44.432
I don't have to choke on
it or anything like that.

00:03:44.432 --> 00:03:47.693
Next, take out your peanut
butter and apply that

00:03:47.693 --> 00:03:50.917
and spread that onto your slice of fruit.

00:03:50.917 --> 00:03:53.449
Then sprinkle on some granola.

00:03:53.449 --> 00:03:56.699
And then place the other
half of fruit on top.

00:03:56.699 --> 00:03:58.858
So, that is snack number two.

00:03:58.858 --> 00:04:02.318
It is so simple to make, but also yummy.

00:04:02.318 --> 00:04:06.219
I love making this as a snack
while I'm watching a movie,

00:04:06.219 --> 00:04:08.262
or before and after a workout,

00:04:08.262 --> 00:04:10.491
so I hope you will enjoy this too.

00:04:10.491 --> 00:04:12.371
So, for this last healthy recipe,

00:04:12.371 --> 00:04:14.484
