making a yogurt parfait.

00:04:14.484 --> 00:04:17.317
This is a tasty breakfast treat to prepare

00:04:17.317 --> 00:04:18.572
if you're always busy.

00:04:18.572 --> 00:04:21.079
I like to prepare this and
store this in my fridge,

00:04:21.079 --> 00:04:24.563
so if I need a quick breakfast,
I have this for on-the-go.

00:04:24.563 --> 00:04:27.116
And it's always good to
have a healthy premade snack

00:04:27.116 --> 00:04:28.417
in the fridge for you.

00:04:28.417 --> 00:04:31.221
To make this, you will need
a yogurt of your choice,

00:04:31.221 --> 00:04:34.467
some fruits and berries, and granola.

00:04:34.467 --> 00:04:36.265
I will also be using some Mason jars.

00:04:36.265 --> 00:04:39.991
You can find this at your local
craft store or supermarket.

00:04:40.991 --> 00:04:45.761
So, first add about two to
four tablespoon of granola.

00:04:45.761 --> 00:04:47.688
Then add in the same amount of yogurt.

00:04:47.688 --> 00:04:49.894
Now, you can add in more
or less if you like.

00:04:49.894 --> 00:04:52.425
This is just something that I prefer.

00:04:52.425 --> 00:04:53.749
Next, add in the fruits.

00:04:53.749 --> 00:04:57.965
I love, love fruit, so I'm
adding half of this jar

00:04:57.965 --> 00:05:00.923
with all the yummy fruits that I like.

00:05:00.923 --> 00:05:04.035
And then, lastly, drizzle on some honey.

00:05:04.035 --> 00:05:06.124
It's optional. You don't have to do it.

00:05:06.124 --> 00:05:10.448
But I like to have that extra
natural sweetness to this,

00:05:10.448 --> 00:05:13.328
and honey just makes this so tasty.

